DTE ENERGY SUPPLY, INC. FERC ELECTRIC TARIFF VOLUME No. 1 MARKET BASED RATES
DTE ENERGY SUPPLY, INC. FERC ELECTRIC TARIFF VOLUME No. 1 MARKET BASED RATES
Availability and Character of Service: DTE Energy Supply, Inc. ("Seller") makes available electric capacity and/or energy under this rate schedule for wholesale sales to purchasers with whom Seller has contracted.
Rates: All rates for sales under this rate schedule shall be established by agreement between Seller and the customer under the applicable service agreement.
General Terms and Conditions: A. Acceptance of service by a customer pursuant to a service agreement hereunder binds the customer to the provisions of this rate schedule and to the terms of the applicable service agreement.
B. The rights of Seller and a customer to seek changes to the rates or other terms and conditions of service initially agreed upon between them shall be governed by the applicable service agreement.
C. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
D. Seller Category: Seller is a Category 2 seller in the Central Region, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a). Seller is a Category 1 seller in the Northeast Region, Southeast Region, Southwest Power Pool Region, Southwest Region and Northwest Region, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a).
E. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: In DTE Edison America, Inc., 84 FERC 61,028, at 4 (1998) Seller was granted (1) waiver of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission's regulations, except as to sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; (2) waiver of Parts 41, 101 and 141 of the Commission's accounting and reporting regulations, except Sections 141.14 and 141.15; and (3) blanket authorization for all future issuances of securities or assumptions of liabilities pursuant to Part 34 of the Commission's regulations.
